metadata.name: Un1 #101
metadata.description:
Un1 is inspired by Unicode block element characters, and my love of minimal and monochromatic art. 

With Un1 I was looking for the final result to have a slightly degraded or low-res look. To that end the pixel density is intentionally set low, (saved images [s] will be based on your browser window size) so that when the piece is enlarged or printed the output has a degraded look.

This artwork was coded using the p5.js library

metadata.name: Snell's Artifacts #97
metadata.description:
Snell's artifacts are imaginary geometric objects created using Snell's and Descartes' laws of optics that define the behavior of a ray of light passing from one transparent medium to another.

By applying these laws to extreme parameters, beyond what the real world is capable of producing and with a high level of variability, we open the door to a new world.

In order to keep some control over this extreme and crazy world, the grid within which the rays evolve is divided into several squares. Each of these squares limits the grid settings at that location.

In order to be able to generate a Snell Artifact, 1 to 6 million rays are created. It may take a while. So be patient while these radii are calculated.




Keyboard commands:
[S]: Saves a PNG image of 4000x4000 pixels without glow filter
[SHIFT + S]: Saves a 4000x4000 pixel PNG image and applies a glow filter (may take a long time depending on your system)

URL parameters:
Add the parameter size=N to generate an image of NxN pixels (glow effect will be disabled by default)
Add the parameter glow=true to apply a glow effect to the image




Artist: Estienne
July 2022

metadata.name: Linetract #123
metadata.description:
Art unites people, the same is also true with Artists.

"Linetract" is a collaborative work of two different artist: @Jolie__Michel and @Uniray_net 
Different backgrounds, different styles, same passion for creativity and Art!

"Linetract" is an abstract composition of simple shapes forms and colors, merged into a final minimal and hopefully aesthetic interesting result :)

CONTROLS

KEYS:

- 1-4: Set resolution from 1x to 4x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

Made with p5js and custom shaders

Collaboration project by @Jolie__Michel and @Uniray_net
© January 2023

metadata.name: primordial soup #206
metadata.description:
1024 kinematic automata that imitate living organisms, leaving behind a trace of paint before going extinct. Blotches of paint are deposited by these nodes that attract and repulse each other according to rules based on their color and size.

Short description of features:
- mood: the palette
- tone: the noisiness
- flow: the number of neighbors affecting each node
- brow: the brush size
- delirium: brush modifier
- distancing: kinetic rule modifier

Each feature is equally likely - rarity is in the eye of the beholder.

@balidani

metadata.name: The String #359
metadata.description:
|| Anniversary project for FX(hash) 1st birthday ||

Each virtual object consists of 365 lights.
Each light represents one day of the year.

We go through every single day, thinking it's all crucial. Yet, from a perspective, it all gets compressed into a single thread. Some of the events are brighter and more memorable. Others just blend or fade away.

I welcomed November 2021 with huge excitement and celebration. The joyful beginning of the month was followed by weeks of misery, anxiety, denial, and acceptance. It was a hard time, but in the long run, it was liberating and started a process of change. Change that happens dynamically to this day.

I couldn't join you last year, but I'm celebrating with you today!



In memory of my Dad.



Donations:
40% – Savepakistan - Flood Relief Fundraiser
10% – Three.js

metadata.name: All Fold: Sketch #35
metadata.description:
'All Fold: Sketch' is a generative system intended to celebrate the writing and artwork that can only be found in the pages of a sketchbook. The project itself is much like a sketch, and attempts to represent the spirit of a work-in-progress.

The fold is included as a reminder that there is always another page.

In the context of the market, the pricing of this project is intended to offer an enjoyable minting experience, while giving the opportunity to contribute to important charities.

- 60% of any primary sales will be split between "Girls Who Code" and "Cure Parkinson's"
- 60% of any royalties will be split between "Girls Who Code" and "Cure Parkinson's"

The aesthetics of this project were directly inspired by the works of Gunta Stölzl, Anni Albers, Gertrud Arndt, Kenneth Martin, and Josef Albers.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2023.
